# Unpatched inputs are "treated like 0 V signals". Here input1 and input3 are
# patched but input2 is not: N is the highest patched index (3), and position 2
# (input2) contributes 0 V.
# SPEC-GAP: the manual only says unpatched inputs are 0 V and "the last input"
# is the last patched; it does not explicitly address gaps. We take N = highest
# patched index and read unpatched middle inputs as their 0.0 default.
#   input1=0.6, input2=(unpatched, 0), input3=0.9, N=3, N-1=2:
#   fade 0    -> p=0.0 -> input1                 = 0.6
#   fade 0.25 -> p=0.5 -> 0.5*0.6 + 0.5*0        = 0.3
#   fade 0.5  -> p=1.0 -> input2 (0)             = 0.0
#   fade 1.0  -> p=2.0 -> input3                 = 0.9
patch <<<
[crossfader]
    input1 = I1
    input3 = I3
    fade   = I4
    output = O1
>>>
@0 set I1 0.6
@0 set I3 0.9
@0 set I4 0
@0 expect O1 0.6
@1 set I4 0.25
@1 expect O1 0.3
@2 set I4 0.5
@2 expect O1 0
@3 set I4 1
@3 expect O1 0.9
